---
import DocsLayout from "@/layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout>
  <div class="space-y-6">
    <div>
      <h1 class="scroll-m-20 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        Introduction
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-muted-foreground">
        Welcome to the Palette UI documentation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <p>
        Palette UI is a beautifully designed component library for building
        modern web applications with Astro and React. It provides a set of
        accessible, reusable, and composable components that make it easy to
        create stunning user interfaces.
      </p>

      <h2 class="scroll-m-20 pt-4 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Key Features
      </h2>
      <ul class="ml-6 list-disc space-y-2">
        <li>
          <strong>Fully Typed:</strong> Built with TypeScript for a better developer
          experience.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Accessible:</strong> Components follow WAI-ARIA guidelines.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Customizable:</strong> Easily theme and style components to match
          your brand.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Responsive:</strong> Designed to work on devices of all sizes.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Fast:</strong> Optimized for performance and minimal bundle size.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="scroll-m-20 pt-4 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Built with modern tools
      </h2>
      <p>Palette UI is built with:</p>
      <ul class="ml-6 list-disc space-y-2">
        <li>
          <a href="https://astro.build" class="text-primary hover:underline"
            >Astro</a
          > - The web framework for content-driven websites
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://react.dev" class="text-primary hover:underline"
            >React</a
          > - For interactive UI components
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://tailwindcss.com" class="text-primary hover:underline"
            >Tailwind CSS</a
          > - For utility-first styling
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://ui.shadcn.com" class="text-primary hover:underline"
            >shadcn/ui</a
          > - For beautiful component design patterns
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="scroll-m-20 pt-4 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Getting Started
      </h2>
      <p>
        To get started with Palette UI, check out the <a
          href="/docs/installation"
          class="text-primary hover:underline">Installation</a
        > guide.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
